post_text: To help contain the spread of the coronavirus and practice the social distancing that is recommended by the CDC, there will be no student attendance days next week, Monday, March 16th through Friday, March 20th, the earliest students could return is 3/30 after spring break. We will update families when we have a solid return date. We've gotten assurance from the commissioner that we can convert student contact days to staff in-service days and we will not need to extend the school year. Teachers will be in touch next week regarding how we plan to continue instructional delivery during the closure. Thank you for your understanding and patience.
text: To help contain the spread of the coronavirus and practice the social distancing that is recommended by the CDC, there will be no student attendance days next week, Monday, March 16th through Friday, March 20th, the earliest students could return is 3/30 after spring break. We will update families when we have a solid return date. We've gotten assurance from the commissioner that we can convert student contact days to staff in-service days and we will not need to extend the school year. Teachers will be in touch next week regarding how we plan to continue instructional delivery during the closure. Thank you for your understanding and patience.

post_text:
Congrats to our very own Rick Hess for receiving the Technology Leadership Award at the 2020 ASTE Conference.

ASTE Tech Support of the Year Award
It is the intent of the ASTE Tech Support of the Year Award to recognize Alaskans who help teachers/faculty find and use technology to support academic goals, which may include helping with hardware. Nominees may include technology integration specialists, instructional web support, database integration support, or others who work behind the scenes to support educators who work directly with students. To be eligible for this award, the nominee must spend less than 75% of his/her day in direct instruction.

post_text: On Tuesday, February 25th at 7 pm we will have a School Board meeting in the school library. During the School Board meeting, we will be discussing issues which include the first reading of the FY 21 budget, school calendar, a proposed middle school basketball trip, waiver of the – 10-degree travel rule, and the hiring of a new teacher, track coach, and technology director. All interested are encouraged to attend.

All interested are encouraged to attend.

post_text: The Skagway School Board Policy Committee will meet On February 14th at noon in the school library. During the meeting, the committee will review Skagway School District policies 6146-6190 which include the topics of graduation requirements, school-sponsored trips, homework, makeup work, individualized education, special education, the selection and evaluation of instructional material, internet use, student mental health, child find, Title I programs, and vocational education. The committee will also be discussing a new facility use agreement, planned absence, and attendance waiver, and policies to accompany a possible new bus. Everyone is welcomed to attend.

post_text: On Tuesday, January 28th we will be having a Community Forum and a School Board meeting in the school library. The Community Forum starts at 6 pm. During the Community Forum, we will be discussing the 2020-2021 district calendar and the Skagway School District Mission and Vision Statements. The School Board Meeting will then start at 7 pm. During the school board meeting, we will be discussing a couple of student travel opportunities, the hiring of a new 1st-grade teacher, exploring school kitchen addition concepts, and authorizing the Don Hather Wall of Fame and the Christopher Maggio Memorial Skagway School Board Scholarship. All interested are encouraged to attend.

On Friday, November 8th we will be having a Policy Committee meeting at noon in the School Library. During the meeting, we will be reviewing policies 6000-6146 and the facility use agreement policy. The 6000 policy section review includes topics regarding how student achievement is defined, school calendar, crisis response plan, curriculum development and evaluation, high school graduation requirements and interscholastic competition. All interested are encouraged to attend.



The full policy manual can be found at https://boardpolicyonline.com/?b=skagway

post_text:
The Skagway School Board is doing something unique to honor Skagway High Alumni who have served our country in the armed forces. Later this year we plan to install the ’Skagway Alumni Wall of Honor’ that will list the names, branch of the military, and years of service for all Skagway High School graduates. We’ve begun to compile a list, but could use some help to ensure accuracy and inclusion. If you or someone you know graduated from Skagway High School and served in the military please contact the school with the information listed above.
To respect the privacy of our veterans please don’t list names or dates as a comment on this post; rather please contact the school office @ (907) 983-2960 or email skgschoff@skagwayschool.org
